body:
Its bronze, i could play adc ww full ap and still win a game.

Yet if i go off meta like i dunno teemo support suddenly everything i say and do is invalidated?

&quot;you should push the lane so jhin has to farm under tower he has a reload mechanic that will deny him farm, and with my blind i can make it so he only gets 1 or 2 cs per wave&quot;

&quot;Stfu your teemo support i just want to farm&quot;

Needless to say the adc fed that game and we lost.

But it raised a question, why in an elo where no one knows jack shit about the game, do people stick so true to the meta so as to throw games if they see an off meta pick.
